<html lang='en'>
  <head>
    <meta charset='UTF-8' />
    <title>Power of Attorney</title>
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        font-size: 14px;
        line-height: 1.6;
        padding: 40px;
        color: #000;
      }
      h1 {
        text-align: center;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        margin-bottom: 30px;
      }
      .section {
        margin-bottom: 20px;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>POWER OF ATTORNEY</h1>

    <div class='section'>
      {{city}},
      {{date}}, 2025
    </div>

    <div class='section'>
      I,
      {{fullName}}, born on
      {{birthDate}}, Tax Identification Number:
      {{tin}}, residing at
      {{address}}, passport:
      {{passport}}, issued on
      {{passportIssueDate}}, being fully aware of the meaning of my actions and acting voluntarily, based on a prior
      agreement, hereby authorize
      {{representativeName}}, born on
      {{representativeBirthDate}}, Tax Identification Number:
      {{representativeTIN}}, residing at
      {{representativeAddress}},
    </div>

    <div class='section'>
      TO BE MY REPRESENTATIVE AND ACT ON MY BEHALF before third parties in all relevant enterprises, institutions, and
      organizations, regardless of their jurisdiction, in particular in
      {{authoritiesList}}
      â€” with all necessary powers to resolve matters related to the privatization and registration of ownership rights
      to the apartment located at:
      {{propertyAddress}}, to obtain the necessary documents and their duplicates, and to further DISPOSE of the
      aforementioned property (sale, exchange, lease) on terms and at a price at her discretion, with the right to enter
      into and sign on my behalf sales agreements, lease agreements, preliminary agreements, agreements for amendments
      and/or supplements to the aforementioned agreements, termination agreements, and so on.
    </div>

    <div class='section'>
      For this purpose, I authorize her to submit and receive on my behalf all necessary certificates, documents,
      applications, technical documentation, reports, extracts, copies, permits, registration and ownership documents,
      including ownership certificates for real estate, extracts/information from the State Register of Property Rights
      to Real Estate regarding the registration of ownership rights; to submit applications on my behalf to the relevant
      authorities and institutions, including applications for issuance of duplicate documents, registration of property
      rights and encumbrances, statements about marital status and/or personal ownership rights, error corrections; to
      receive any necessary documents, including ownership documents and their duplicates, ownership certificates (or
      their duplicates), information certificates and/or extracts from the State Register of Property Rights to Real
      Estate; to sign documents and receive them on my behalf, to enter into and sign preliminary agreements, sales
      contracts, agreements on amendments and/or supplements to said contracts, lease agreements, termination
      agreements, etc.; to open and close accounts on my behalf in any banking institutions, to make non-cash
      settlements, receive funds due to me, pay document processing fees, administrative fees, state duties, taxes, and
      other necessary payments, and to perform all other actions related to this Power of Attorney.
    </div>

    <div class='section'>
      This Power of Attorney is issued with the right of substitution and is valid for THREE YEARS, until
      {{validUntil}}.
    </div>

    <div class='section'>
      Signature: ____________________
      {{fullName}}
    </div>
  </body>
</html>